        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Opera 11 Web Browser'); ?>
        <p>Opera 11 (codenamed <em>Kjevik</em>) was released on 16 December 2010 with new features including extensions, tab stacking, visual mouse gestures, new installer (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows', 'OS'); ?> only) and safety improvements to the address field.</p>
        <p>In addition, the content blocker list now can be synchronized through Opera Link. It also passes the Acid3 Test as of 22 January 2011.</p>
        <p>On 12 April 2011, Opera 11.10 (codenamed <em>Barracuda</em>) was released. It contains many fixes "under the hood", such as improved Turbo Mode, a plug-in installation wizard and a rewritten Speed Dial. Opera 11.10 was updated to use the new Presto 2.8 Rendering Engine.</p>
        <p>On 18 May 2011, the final version of Opera 11.11 was released with improvements to security.</p>
        <p>On 28 June 2011, Opera 11.50 (codename <em>Swordfish</em>) was released.</p>
        <p>Equipped with the rendering engine Presto 2.9.168 featuring up to 20% faster rendering of CSS and SVG, support for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('HTML5', 'WD'); ?> tags , Session History and Navigation, it also features extensions in the Speed Dial, support for password sync in Opera Link and an updated <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('UI', 'IT'); ?>.</p>
        <p>On 6 December 2011, Opera 11.60 (codename <em>Tunny</em>) was released.</p>
        <p>Updated with the newest rendering engine Presto 2.10.229, this update features several changes including a UI revamp of the email interface, a new address field with star feature, and several "under the hood" as new HTML5 tags and parsing implementations, full ECMAScript 5.1 support.</p>
        <p>This version also implemented the JSON API geo-location of Google.</p>
        <p>On 24 January 2012, Opera 11.61 was released with improvements to security and stability.</p>
        <p>On 27 March 2012, Opera 11.62 was released with security and stability improvements, bug fixes and performance improvements.</p>
        <p>On 17 April 2012, Opera 11.63 was released. It was a Mac exclusive release, contrary to belief that <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Apple', 'C'); ?> had prematurely flipped the switch, making this release available for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Mac', 'ITH'); ?> users ahead of <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows', 'OS'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Linux', 'OS'); ?> customers.</p>
        <p>On May 10, 2012, Opera 11.64 was released, with stability, bug fixes and security improvements.</p>
